    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, an apex of front-midship design. This example features the legendary 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, utilizing its factory sequential twin-turbocharger configuration for seamless power delivery and high-RPM efficiency. The longitudinal power plant is paired with a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring precise torque distribution. The chassis remains exceptionally stiff, riding on its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension with aluminum control arms to minimize unsprung mass. Finished in flawless Montego Blue Mica, the exterior retains a factory-perfect finish with no signs of oxidation. The interior is equally pristine, featuring uncracked plastics and tight seat bolsters. Meticulously maintained with verified compression across both rotors and a leak-free vacuum system, this is a rare, unmolested specimen for the serious enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
